I have received e-mails daily telling me what  a bad person I am for telling the truth and warning others.  But still this is a true account of what has happened to me for trying to make an honest deal with a dishonest person selling bad ammo out of Fernely. title: For Sale:  Historical Firearm from the Flathead
postcontent:
This weapon has 3 layers of very cool history to it, first off it is a !860's era French  Tabatière muzzle loader later converted in Belgium to a 10 gauge shotgun then exported to North America as a HUNTER model and not ZULU.The gun has a Tag that Sam Johns wrote a description of the gun on it and by whom owned it. Second Layer of History on this gun is that it was in the Same Johns gun collection that consisted of 450 some guns all of which were donated to the Montana Historical Society in Helena except for this one which was picked up in 1957. Sam Johns was born in Wales in 1866 and came to Montana and the Flathead in the 1880s and was one of Kalispells first Merchants in the early 1890's and previously had lived in Demersville ,he recorded the history of the Flathead and was a collector of historical Firearms. he has 10 volumes of his research and memoirs at the Mike Mansfield Library in Missoula. Google him,very interesting man. The third layer of history is that this gun was originally owned by Tom Mcgovern, whom Mcgoverns Bay was named after which was renamed Somers Bay on flatehead Lake. Tom Mcgovern was a Irish Immigrant who sold all the Land where the Town of Somers now sits to John O'brian who built the town of Somers and the Saw mill.Historical home in Kalispell the Mcgovern/Karcher home was built by Tom Mcgovern.
Gun has a Helluva lot of neat history to it and is a Fantastic conversation piece and would make a great wall hanger. I wasn't able to show other information on opposite side of Tag as I only had 3 picture options,will provide to you if interested.No trades cash only. Asking 120.00  This is a steal folks!

title: For Sale:  FN Tactical Police Shotgun Package, tons of ammo, and accessories
postcontent:
For sale is a lightly used FN Tactical Police Shotgun. The gun originally had a 4 plus 1 capacity. It has an integrated top rail and AR-15 style front and rear sights. It also utilizes a AR-15 stock and pistol grip. The gun is based on a Winchester 1300 action and is extremely smooth. This is the last of the pump shotguns made by FN, and the dealer stock ran out about six years ago. Several non-permanent additions have been added to the base gun. An EoTech clone was placed on the rail and is included. A Tac-Star six round side saddle has been mounted to the receiver, as well as the addition of a Tapco S.A.W. style pistol grip. This grip is a bit wider than a standard AR-15 style pistol grip, and helps tame the recoil of the 12 gauge. The trigger guard has also been replaced with a Magpul enhanced polymer trigger guard to reduce sharp edges. An ambidextrous sling plate has been added as well as a collapsible stock. To that collapsible stock a Mesa Tactical SOCOM six round side saddle has been added. Also a magazine tube extension has been fitted to increase the capacity to eight rounds plus one. The gun will carry a total of 21 rounds with a loaded chamber. All of the original parts are included with the purchase of the gun. The barrel is 18.5 inches long and compensated with a breaching muzzle. 

Also included is a Blackhawk Shotgunner vest. I used this in the early days of three gun before I had access to items specifically designed for the sport. It has 3 AR-15 magazine pouches holding a total of six thirty round magazines. On the opposite side it has two pouches with elastic loops that hold a total of 28 rounds of 12 gauge in an easily accessed position. There are also just under 300 rounds of 12 gauge ammo included. Types include law enforcement grade buckshot, slugs, and less lethal pepper ball rounds. Also birdshot and a couple of different types of Brenneke slugs. This package is a one stop solution for those looking for a great home defense gun, or wanting to get into three gun matches. The asking price is $1100 or best offer for everything. At this point I am not looking for trades, or wanting to separate the package. For a fast response you can text me at 6 two 3- 2 6 one – six 2 four seven. 

Thanks for looking!
